[vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="1042" img_size="full"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]

PRIVACY POLICY

TIt is our policy to respect your privacy regarding any information we may collect while operating our website.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]
  • Personal information Before using certain parts of any Printshop.com or ordering Products, you must complete an online registration form. During registration, you will be prompted to provide to us certain personal information, including but not limited to Users (your/company) name, shipping and billing address, phone number, email address, and credit card number. In addition, we may also ask you for your/Customers country of residence and/or organizations country of operation, so we can comply with applicable laws and regulations, and for your gender. These kinds of personal information are used for billing purposes, to fulfill orders, to communicate about order and Printshop, and for internal marketing purposes. If we encounter a problem when processing the order, your personal information may be used to contact you. By registering at Printshop.com, you agree that all information provided in the registration data is true and accurate and that you will maintain and update this information as required in order to keep it current, complete, and accurate. Printshop may collect statistics about the behavior of visitors to its Site. Printshop may display this information publicly or provide it to others. However, Printshop does not disclose personal information other than as described here. If you are a registered user of a Printshop Site and have supplied your email address, Printshop may occasionally send you an email to tell you about new features, new Products, solicit your feedback. Printshop takes all measures reasonably necessary to protect against count for any reason, in our sole discretion.
  • Disclosure of information We do not sell or rent, your personal information to third parties for their marketing purposes without Your explicit consent. We may disclose personal information to respond to legal requirements, enforce our policies, respond to claims that a content violates others rights, or protect anyones rights, property, or safety. We may also share personal information with:Service providers who help with our business operations and assist in the delivery of Products or Services to our users. These service providers are under confidentiality agreements with us;Law enforcement or other government officials in order to investigate, prevent, or take action regarding illegal activities, suspected fraud, violations of law, or as otherwise required by law
  • Security Your account is protected by a password for your privacy and security. You need to prevent unauthorized access to your account and personal information by selecting and protecting your password appropriately and limiting access to your computer and browser by signing off after you have finished accessing your account.
  • Privacy policy changes Although most changes are likely to be minor, Printshop may change its Privacy Policy from time to time, and in Printshops sole discretion. Printshop encourages you to frequently check this page for any changes to its Privacy Policy. Your continued use of this Site after any change in this Privacy Policy will constitute your acceptance of such change.
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]

item.title: Five Best Photo-Printing Sites
item.dc:creator: admin_nb
item.content:encoded:
Digital cameras are fantastic for letting us experiment, take tons of photos, and search for the perfect shot. Digital picture frames and at-home prints are often poor substitutes for real photos. Get a great print at one of these five photo-printing sites.
Once upon a time people took photos and dutifully carted their film down to the photo shop to get developed, waiting to see how the photos turned out. Now people immediately check whether or not the shot was good on the display of their digital camera, and more often than not stuff the photos onto their hard drives or upload them to their Flickr accounts, but never get around to actually printing them and preserving them in a physical form. If youve been meaning to get around to printing more photos and saving them from their fate of digital obscurity, the following five Lifehacker reader-selected sites can help you.
